Another € 400 million for infrastructure
The agreement on three credit lines totaling € 400 million to support education, transport and environmental infrastructure as well as energy was signed in Budapest on Friday by Finance Minister János Veres and Marta Gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB).
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) approved a framework of EUR 300 million for the Hungarian budget financing of transport and environment projects implemented with the support of the Cohesion Fund, with the parties having previously concluded a loan agreement for EUR 100 million, now signed concerns the use of the remaining EUR 200 million.
A loan agreement worth EUR 150 million is also used to finance education-related projects.
