The development of the Bulgarian real estate market is staggering - the attention of the whole of Europe is turning to the previously somewhat neglected Balkan country.
What, where and who is shopping in the still cheapest, but fast-rising EU market so far?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of Re / Max.
Bulgaria is without a doubt the most sought-after Eastern European property purchase destination with its cheap ski apartments and seaside houses.
Most of the mountains in the area are Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitoša, on the sea coast then Albena, Golden Sands, Sunny Beach, the ancient towns of Sozobol and Nessebar, but more and more people are also looking for real estate around Kavarna and Balchik.
