&quot;A common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civic associations, while openly declaring - even armed - the readiness of their members to perform defense tasks (in case of natural disasters, attacks on the homeland, disorder), in addition to the incompetence of police, army , or the state, &quot;he adds.
