Holidays are not free everywhere
In Hungary, days off are precisely set by law, and it has become common practice for working days to move around the holidays, which awaits us less times next year.
Holidays are not uniform in the European Union or in America.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and public holidays.
Public holidays are usually linked to church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year with us: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year are holidays - for the New Year, so that people can relax after New Year&#39;s Eve.
During the year, we otherwise have a total of eleven holidays.
The national holiday is March 15, celebrating the revolution of 1848 and October 23, the memorial day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1, work, on November 1 and 2, we remember deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, the two-day holidays are Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
Because our state, national, or religious holidays rarely fall on weekends, it has become a practice to move a workday in cases where we only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price for extended weekends, however, is that the previous Saturdays we stay at work and at school.
For many years, the Minister of Labor has been regulating when the day immediately preceding or following the holiday is worked out in a special decree.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and the employees they employ, to public employees and to persons in the public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or, with regard to their purpose, operate even on non-working days.
This year, the work schedule will change only around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, or according to previous experience, most people will &quot;work&quot; the days between Christmas and New Year&#39;s Eve or use the saved holidays.
Next year, several of our holidays fall in the middle or at the end of the week, so there will be fewer transfers of the working day than this year.
For the first time, the calendar changes around Labor Day, so that workers can stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday, April 26, will be a working day, so that Friday, on the contrary, can be a day of rest.
Another move is related to the holiday of October 23: work will take place on Saturday, October 18 instead of Friday the 24th.
However, the end of the year next year will be able to take place entirely in the sign of the holidays, because from December 24 they will have non-stop holidays almost everywhere, even though New Year&#39;s Eve falls on a Wednesday.
