What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, it is necessary to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive the agreed sum insured in a certain amount for taking responsibility for paying damages in the event of an insured event.
Premium is the price of insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driver&#39;s license, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely an accident is to occur, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of inspections, insurance companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journeys and thus the probability that it will have an accident.
As the frequency of rides increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the price of a premium.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best suits his profile as the insured.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and a short holding of a driving license, when they want to negotiate premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount on insurance premiums in order to obtain insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would presuppose the client&#39;s co-participation in the payment of the insured event.
&quot;The part of the indemnity paid by the client will be determined in advance when determining the premium price, the higher the co-participation,&quot; explains Luis Noguera, chief executive officer of First Europe in Spain, an internet insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other road users so that the client insures himself against damage caused by other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendation.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
In contrast, a malus is an increase in said base rate.
&quot;The bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus, &quot;explains Noguera.
After exceeding the limit of twenty-five years, drivers find it easier when they go to take out insurance, as the client&#39;s risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
&quot;Young people are usually unable to benefit from the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident, nor when driving,&quot; says the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when &quot;fear of a newcomer&quot; .
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums (which could be 300 euros) or, with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
&quot;Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,&quot; notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums (amounting to EUR 150) or insurance extended to other road users if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best given our personal situation.
